  "prompt": "Will I get refund after preparation of chart for wait listed ticket?",
  "response": "Whether you get a refund for a waitlisted ticket after chart preparation depends on how far your ticket was from being confirmed and the railway's refund rules. Here's a breakdown:\n\n*   **Fully Waitlisted (GNWL, RLWL, PQWL) and Not Confirmed/Partially Confirmed:** If your ticket remains fully waitlisted or is only partially confirmed after chart preparation, you are eligible for a refund. However, there will be a small deduction as cancellation charges.\n*   **Refund Amount:** The refund amount depends on the cancellation charges levied by the railways, which can vary based on the class of travel and the time of cancellation (in this case, after chart preparation).\n*   **Auto-Cancellation:** Most waitlisted e-tickets are automatically cancelled after chart preparation if they don't get confirmed. The refund is usually processed automatically back to the payment method used for booking.\n*   **Counter Tickets:** For tickets booked at the counter, you typically need to file a TDR (Ticket Deposit Receipt) to claim the refund at the counter within a specified time.\n\n**In summary, you will likely get a refund if your waitlisted ticket doesn't get confirmed after chart preparation, but a cancellation charge will be deducted.**\n\nTo get the most accurate information, it's best to:\n\n*   **Check the IRCTC website or app:** Look for the specific rules regarding waitlisted ticket refunds.\n*   **Contact IRCTC customer care:** They can provide details on your specific ticket and potential refund amount.\n*   **Check the railway's refund policies.**",
